Hi Wenbo,
 
The income variables are adjusted to 2014$ using the CPI-U-RS. You can
see how we did this in our cepr_march_real.do[1] program.
 
Our cepr_march_income_real.do[2] program lists the inflation-adjusted
variable names.
 
Generally these variables add an "r" to the nominal variable name. So
for instance, our nominal variable measuring person's total income is
"incp_all", and our inflation-adjusted version is "rincp_all".
 
